{"id":47059,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Simon_Peyton_Jones","text":"Simon Peyton Jones (1958-) born in South Africa and is a British computer scientist. He does research on (lazy) functional programming languages, such as Haskell. He works at Microsoft Research in Cambridge, England. He is married to Dorothy, a priest in the Church of England. They have six children.\nSimon Peyton Jones, Simon Marlow and others have developed the Glasgow Haskell Compiler, a compiler for Haskell.\nHe has also worked on C--.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"1958","surface_form":"1958","offset":20},{"uri":"South_Africa","surface_form":"South Africa","offset":35},{"uri":"British","surface_form":"British","offset":57},{"uri":"Computer_scientist","surface_form":"computer scientist","offset":65},{"uri":"Research","surface_form":"research","offset":93},{"uri":"Lazy_evaluation","surface_form":"lazy","offset":106},{"uri":"Functional_programming_language","surface_form":"functional","offset":112},{"uri":"Programming_language","surface_form":"programming language","offset":123},{"uri":"Haskell","surface_form":"Haskell","offset":154},{"uri":"Microsoft_Research","surface_form":"Microsoft Research","offset":175},{"uri":"Cambridge","surface_form":"Cambridge","offset":197},{"uri":"England","surface_form":"England","offset":208},{"uri":"Priest","surface_form":"priest","offset":245},{"uri":"Church_of_England","surface_form":"Church of England","offset":259},{"uri":"Simon_Marlow","surface_form":"Simon Marlow","offset":322},{"uri":"Glasgow_Haskell_Compiler","surface_form":"Glasgow Haskell Compiler","offset":365},{"uri":"Compiler","surface_form":"compiler","offset":393},{"uri":"C--","surface_form":"C--","offset":437}]}